column5: That third one is TJ's son with a beard. And Roy's the cute one in the yellow pfd under Lew, right?  JF
LOL..  Thats a post from '96... pictures are cool.. You hasnt outgrown the PFD yet!!
Thats a rockin' cool wind breaker Ben

My first shark and cuda..caught on the same day... 2001 I think...shark is still my personal best big fish..was about 8 ft and about 200 pounds. We were using 30 pound test mono then too!! Got shut out on the tarpons tho.
haha yeah.  It was late Aug but cold as heck up here that year (2004).  That's actually my old gore-tex winter jacket!!  4 years after that pic was taken I ended up buying that boat.
Wow! Seems some things (IE fishermen) do not get better with age.  I love the old photos, I will have to look for some more of mine.

I was cleaning up some files and was browsing through the thumbnails and found some really neat pictures of old ofners and some other stuff i thought i would share...  can anyone guess who these guys are...  these pictures most of em anyway are from when I had a frequent contributors page that I used to update manually.. back in '02                    Should bring back some memories...             And More...                    And more...                        and more...                        and finally...

Boy I didnt realize I was that good looking LOL Wow those are some oldies that one of me was atleast 5 or 6 yrs ago Sure does bring back great memories.. Thanks for the Post TJ Robin Nice Baot Captain Lew!!!!!
Hey I remember some of those pictures.  Ive always liked the first one.  What ever happened to GrilW anyways?
wow some relly nice pictures there! and some really nice fish lol

lol.. nice TJ  okay you can all stop guessing... the 5th pic is me   That was my first time ever on Lac Seul... oh how a few years can have a lot of change.  Who else do I see... both your kids (i think), yeah Girlw, Dan, Rick, speil?, lew, muhmba (Roger something?)... a bunch of red x's.  haha  Thanks for the neat post TJ.
Nice pics
OH OH, maybe I really have been loitering around here too many years, I know pretty near everyone there  Thanks TJ, lotsa great memories in those pictures !!
He's busy picking up ladies at York U.
That looks like a spinning reel in your hand there Robin!!Whats up with that?? Joe
Gregs still here but he's another one who changed his name for some reason, but darned if I can remember what the heck it is.
....Yeah, I've always liked that first one too. But really, who is that skinny fella in the second picture.

Your not!  Wow, I feel special, I got my pic up there twice!  Now, I remember that pic was longgg before my first digital camera, in fact, I recall getting those pictures put on CD at Quinte Photo. If I'm not mistaken, it cost me about 20 bucks for that! The year was 2000
GREAT PICS !! NOT A FAN OF A STRINGER FULL OF STEEL BUT BACK IN THOSE DAYS THERE WAS PLENTY AROUND!!! I ALWAYS HERE FROM THE OLD GUYS THE "BACK IN THE DAY"STORIES  LOL
Great pictures, thanks...
Wow .... thats from 1985 !!!! I'll bet a few OFC'ers werent even born yet  :)
Geez..... I look fat!! LOL! Although I do like my hat  Gerritt
Geezze those were before my pensions kicked in!

That first pic, oh, it can't be you, lol. You've changed bud. I think I know who the fifth pic is. I definately know who 11, 12, and 13 are. 11 and 12 I have met. 18, 19, 20, and 21  are obvious to anyone who has been here for a while, Lew, Jaden, Grilw, Reefhawg.  23 is GaryV 28..........LOL, camillj 35 is Avery 36 is Steve(photoz) 37 is DanC  I think I got all that right. At least I think so.  And Robin, yeah, you were good looking back when, lol.
nice shots, thats one huge sunny your daughter has
LOL>. the secodn one is me... the first one .. lol.. with the "KILL CHAIN"... lol is Spiel...
....Kill Chain....lol.  Gotta admit I love the taste of fresh fish. , mmmmm good.
I could of sworn that was Sonny Bono in the third!
I see some photoshop there
Thanks for bringing those old pics back up TJ, lotsa fun times  there.  Good to see the picture of Gary V again too....he was a great guy and a real asset to this board.

Pretty Cool ... I see what I have missed by not signing up sooner.  Heck - I even recongize a couple of them.  Hey TJ - after a while here, how about posting the names of those in the pics for us newcomers.
